comments: Zubac (LAC) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Lowry (MIA) and any contact is considered marginal.
Herro (MIA) inbounds the ball in less than 5 seconds.
Batum (LAC) deflects the pass and he is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Lowry (MIA) extends his right leg into Zubac (LAC) as he attempts to draw a foul during his jump shot attempt. This play should be assessed as an offensive foul on Lowry (TOR).
Lowry (MIA) swipes down and lightly brushes Jackson's (LAC) leg during the driving shot attempt. The contact is marginal.
George (LAC) jumps vertically and he absorbs the body contact during Adebayo's (MIA) shot attempt near the rim.
Zubac (LAC) delivers contact to Lowry's (MIA) body during his driving shot attempt.
Robinson (MIA) places his hand on Batum's (LAC) side but the marginal contact does not affect Batum's ability to move freely.
George (LAC) gathers the ball and he establishes his left foot as his pivot. He then lifts his pivot foot and brings it back to the floor prior to releasing the pass.
Lowry (MIA) reaches in and makes contact to Jackson's (LAC) arm that affects his ability to maintain control of the ball.
During the loose ball, Jackson (LAC) briefly places his hand on Lowry's (MIA) front and he immediately removes it. The contact is marginal.
Robinson (MIA) commits a take foul on Jackson (LAC).
Mann (LAC) maintains a legal guarding position during Lowry's (MIA) driving shot attempt.
Martin (MIA) commits a take foul on Jackson (LAC).
Following the pass deflection, Adebayo (MIA) holds Batum's (LAC) jersey and the contact affects his FOM.
Lowry (MIA) makes marginal contact with Mann's (LAC) body during his driving shot attempt.
